In 2005, while working for the original McGill family business The North Rocks Greenery, Jon recognised an opportunity. He took on his first Garden Maintenance customer armed with just a pair of secateurs. This idea grew into a thriving local business and expanded to Landscaping.

While under The North Rocks Greenery the business was primarily focused on Landscaping and Maintenance for the Hills district of Sydney. The McGill family was then forced to re-brand and re-invent the business following the sale of the Nursery. Despite many challenges, that change has acted as a catalyst for the business, still under the McGill Family. Under it's new name, Looking Up Landscapes, the business has moved away from Garden Maintenance to incorporate more extensive Landscaping services and has shifted their area of work to encompass the Central Coast, Lake Macquarie area, the Hunter Valley and Newcastle.
